			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We're only going to be using POSIX signal handling on Linux, not on Mac OS X.  Furthermore, the Windows version of nacl_signal was never secure for handling untrusted faults on x86-64 Windows.

To remove the Mac/Windows versions of nacl_signal, we will first have to change code that uses them.  This includes sel_ldr's built-in debug stub, and platform_qualify/win/nacl_dep_qualify.c.
